    "title" : "SigScale CSE - Resource Inventory",
    "description" : "# TMF639 Resource Inventory Management\n\nSigScale uses the standard TM Forum [OpenAPIs](https://www.tmforum.org/open-apis/) for open interoperability. The TMF639 API is used in SigScale CSE to represent logical resources such as tables and table rows.\n\n# Prefix Tables\n\nThe Service Logic Execution Environment (SLEE) includes a general purpose facility for prefix matching tables. Multiple key-value tables may be created, using this API, where the key is a string representing a prefix. A typical use case is matching of dialed digits.\n\n## Table\n\nA table is respresented by a `Resource` entity in the inventory. The `name` attribute will be used by Service Logic Processing Programs (SLP) to select a table. Use the `PrefixTable` `ResourceSpecification` (id=1).\n\n## Row\n\nEach row in a table is an individual `Resource` entity with a `resourceRelationship` to the containing table. Use the `PrefixTableRow` `ResourceSpecification` (id=2). The `prefix` characteristic value represents the string to match while the result of the match is provided by the value of the characteristic named `value`.",
